result.name: Tai Hing

reviews.text: The Japanese place on the first floor is awesome! Unlimited salad and miso soup.

Here is one of the fall-back eating place options I would consider if no more than four of my family members would eat out. Proper restaurants are often not value for money and other fast food chains might not have vacant seats. After months of absence, I came here again for an early lunch on March 2, 2018 just to remember that the char kway teow set (at HK$57), though objectively very good by Hong Kong and Asian standards, was a bit spicy for me!
